#. type: Title =
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sharpening a photo\n"
msgstr "写真をシャープ化する\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:8
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-Sharpen-en.png) The **Sharpen** tool allows you to "
"sharpen all or parts of your photo using a technique based on the tradition "
"of using an unsharp mask in a darkroom to increase the perception of "
"sharpness by emphasizing edges."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:11
msgid ""
"Most digital photos have a slight softness in the fine details and would "
"benefit from sharpening."
msgstr "ほとんどのデジタル写真は細部のティテールがわずかに柔らかいため、シャープ化が有用です。"

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "To sharpen your photo:\n"
msgstr "写真をシャープ化するには:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:16
msgid "![image](images/Button-Sharpen.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.  Click the sharpen tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Editing.html).\n"
"    (A new sharpen tool will appear at the top of the [tool\n"
"    stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  Use the sliders to adjust the sharpness:\n"
"    -   The Amount slider controls how much sharpening is done.\n"
"    -   The Radius slider controls how widely the sharpening effect is\n"
"        done around each pixel.\n"
"    -   The Threshold slider controls how different each pixel must be\n"
"        from its surrounding area before it is considered an edge pixel\n"
"        and therefore sharpened.\n"
msgstr ""
"1.  Click the sharpen tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Editing.html).\n"
"    (A new sharpen tool will appear at the top of the [tool\n"
"    stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  Use the sliders to adjust the sharpness:\n"
"    -   The Amount slider controls how much sharpening is done.\n"
"    -   The Radius slider controls how widely the sharpening effect is\n"
"        done around each pixel.\n"
"    -   The Threshold slider controls how different each pixel must be\n"
"        from its surrounding area before it is considered an edge pixel\n"
"        and therefore sharpened.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""
"3.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Sharpen.markdown.txt:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** It's best to be viewing your photo fully zoomed-in before\n"
"sharpening it by selecting View \\> Actual Pixels.\n"
msgstr ""

